# RunAnywhere Commons - Exported Symbols
#
# Curated Apple `-exported_symbols_list` for `librac_commons.{a,dylib}`.
# Consumed by `sdk/runanywhere-commons/CMakeLists.txt` and applied at link time
# when commons is built as a shared library (static archives ignore the option).
# Each entry must include the leading underscore (Apple linker convention).
#
# To audit drift vs. RAC_API-decorated declarations in the commons headers:
#   scripts/validation/check_rac_api_exports.sh            # advisory report
#   scripts/validation/check_rac_api_exports.sh --strict   # CI gate (exit 1)
#
# TODO(v0.21): As of 2026-05-05 the include tree exposes 955 RAC_API-decorated
# decls total; 465 are shipped via this exports list, and 490 remain as
# internalization candidates not called by any SDK today. Those should either
# have RAC_API stripped from the header or be relocated to `src/.../internal.h`.
# Once that cleanup lands, wire `check_rac_api_exports.sh --strict` into
# `scripts/validation/run_commons_proto_checks.sh` as a CI gate.
#
# Note: backend-conditional symbols (rac_rag_*, rac_backend_rag_*,
# rac_backend_whisperkit_coreml_*, rac_whisperkit_coreml_stt_set_callbacks)
# are deliberately NOT listed here even though SDKs call them — the shared
# linker would reject the list when those backends are not compiled. When
# commons is built as a dynamic lib, backend-specific symbols come from
# per-backend shared libraries (librac_backend_rag.so, RABackendLLAMACPP,
# etc.) which already export them with default visibility.
#
# Symbols declared RAC_API but without a commons-side implementation
# (`rac_vad_start`, `rac_vad_stop`, `rac_vad_reset` in
# include/rac/features/vad/rac_vad_service.h) are also intentionally absent
# — those are stale declarations that should be removed from the headers
# as a follow-up.

# Audio Utilities — internal helpers (PCM/WAV plumbing for backends and
# tests). Audio bytes leaving the SDK travel inside generated proto results.

# Memory and Core
_rac_alloc
_rac_free
_rac_strdup
_rac_init
_rac_is_initialized
_rac_shutdown
_rac_get_version
_rac_log

